commentable_entity.ask: Demand  Disney Keep Johnny Depp In Pirates of the Carribean
commentable_entity.title: Walt Disney Studios: Demand  Disney Keep Johnny Depp In Pirates of the Carribean
commentable_entity.description:
(Please do NOT donate to this!!! They are not needed and will not help. Just need as many signatures as possible! THANKS!!!)

Johnny Depp will no longer play Captain Jack Sparrow in the Pirates of the Caribbean film series, Disney producer Sean Bailey confirmed.

The actor came under fire in 2016 after his ex-wife, Amber Heard, claimed he domestically abused her. Depp denied the allegations and the case was settled in the same year.

Whether or not the above incident is the reason behind Disney's decision to pull Johnny Depp from future POTC movies, it does not diminish the fact that Johnny Depp made the POTC movies the incredible success that they are. POTC would not have the following that it does without him. As such, it will be a disappointment to fans of the movie if he is dropped from future POTC films. 

Johnny Depp has even gone so far as to show up at children's hospitals, dressed as Captain Jack in full costume, visiting for hours and never breaking character. 
To remove him from any further POTC movies is unthinkable.

We are asking Disney to reconsider their decision and keep Johnny Depp on in his role as Captain Jack, in any and all future POTC movies.
commentable_entity.letter_body: Demand  Disney Keep Johnny Depp In Pirates of the Carribean

comment: Honestly I don’t see the reason to even support Disney anymore if they are doing a stupid stunt like this. It’s like driving a car with no wheels. There’s just no point to doing it if it will just make things worse. Disney if you carry on to delete CAPRAIN jack sparrow Disneyland and all of the Disney franchise will always and forever be the WORST PLACE ON EARTH
commentable_entity.ask: Demand  Disney Keep Johnny Depp In Pirates of the Carribean
commentable_entity.title: Walt Disney Studios: Demand  Disney Keep Johnny Depp In Pirates of the Carribean
commentable_entity.description:
(Please do NOT donate to this!!! They are not needed and will not help. Just need as many signatures as possible! THANKS!!!)

Johnny Depp will no longer play Captain Jack Sparrow in the Pirates of the Caribbean film series, Disney producer Sean Bailey confirmed.

The actor came under fire in 2016 after his ex-wife, Amber Heard, claimed he domestically abused her. Depp denied the allegations and the case was settled in the same year.

Whether or not the above incident is the reason behind Disney's decision to pull Johnny Depp from future POTC movies, it does not diminish the fact that Johnny Depp made the POTC movies the incredible success that they are. POTC would not have the following that it does without him. As such, it will be a disappointment to fans of the movie if he is dropped from future POTC films. 

Johnny Depp has even gone so far as to show up at children's hospitals, dressed as Captain Jack in full costume, visiting for hours and never breaking character. 
To remove him from any further POTC movies is unthinkable.

We are asking Disney to reconsider their decision and keep Johnny Depp on in his role as Captain Jack, in any and all future POTC movies.
commentable_entity.letter_body: Demand  Disney Keep Johnny Depp In Pirates of the Carribean
